(iii)  preparing a TA inception report outlining methodological approaches, TA issues 
and options, data sources, survey questionnaires, work plan, results framework, 
and implementation issues; 
(iv)  organizing  a  TA  inception  workshop  to  discuss  the  TA  inception  report, 
preliminary findings, and other issues with key stakeholders across the network;  
(v)  determining a clear and coherent communication structure and monitoring and 
evaluation process to support the steering committee; 
(vi)  reviewing  and  designing  new  project  planning,  design,  and  management  
systems and procedures, ensuring that consideration is taken into account of 
climate change, and the impact of climate change on project design; 
(vii)  obtaining approval from DTCI and state utilities for the enhanced systems and 
procedures with support of the steering committee and change champions; 
(viii)  preparing codification of new systems and procedures in written format including 
manuals on (i)planning and civil works; (ii)contracting of civil works; and (iii) 
management and supervision of civil works; 
(ix)  implementing new systems and procedures within DTCI;  
(x)  assessing and monitoring effectiveness of new systems and procedures, and 
advising on readjustment as required;  
(xi)  establishing  DTCI  change  team  comprising  department  heads  and  change 
champions, and developing a communication plan and meeting schedule;  
(xii)  designing a change management program and communication plan based on an 
analysis of systems, procedures, and human resources;  
(xiii)  undertaking a comprehensive assessment of the capacity of all DTCI staff and 
long-term consultants and contractors against their roles and accountabilities and 
the systems and procedures DTCI and state utilities agreed upon for project 
planning, design, and management; 
(xiv)  reviewing capacity assessment gaps;  
(xv)  developing a capacity building work program for each individual;  
(xvi)  determining  department-  and  division-specific  capacity  building  programs, 
identifying all training opportunities available, including formal, informal, and on-
the-job training;  
(xvii)  assisting ADB in recruiting an infrastructure management specialist and other 
short-term consultants, and supervising and assessing their performance; 
(xviii)  managing the implementation of the capacity building program, including on-the-
job training and specialist technical training;  
(xix)  delivering components of the capacity building program in conjunction with the 
infrastructure management specialist; 
(xx)  monitoring and assessing all aspects of the capacity building program against 
defined  deliverables throughout the term of the TA; 
(xxi)  ensuring institutionalization of the training and capacity building program through 
documentation and systematization of the program within the human resource 
function of the national and state governments; 
(xxii)  preparing  and  disseminating  communication  materials  on  the  institutional 
framework throughout the term of TA; 
(xxiii)  designing  and  implementing  a  new  contracts  procedures  manual  within  12 
months of TA inception; 
(xxiv)  undertaking  a  comprehensive  review  of  change  management  and  capacity 
building; 

